<subSubSection id="C361C3D1502AFFD1FF33FA21FF093F90" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="21" pageId="2" pageNumber="19" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BC4905A502AFFD7FF33FA21FB6A391D" blockId="2.[151,1437,1302,2012]" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis id="B90F4C48502AFFD7FF33FA21FE9C3BD9" bold="true" box="[199,335,1446,1472]" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">Description</emphasis>
: Male 
<quantity id="4C833DBF502AFFD7FE6DFA20FE043BD8" box="[409,471,1447,1473]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="19" unit="mm" value="7.0">7 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="4C833DBF502AFFD7FDEEFA21FD8B3BD8" box="[538,600,1446,1473]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="19" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
wide (with parapodia, without chaetae), with 21 segments, flat. Living colour purple-red (
<figureCitation id="13408CDF502AFFD7FEECFA4DFE8B3BFD" box="[280,344,1482,1508]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,181,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[164,1423,181,1865]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Branchinotogluma nikkoensis sp. nov., holotype. A, whole specimen, dorsal view; B, whole specimen, ventral view; C, dorsal view of anterior; D, ventral view of posterior; E, elytrum; F, pharynx, frontal view; G, pharynx, lateral view; H, papillae of pharynx. Abbreviation: ma, median antenna; p. palps; tc, tentacular cirri; pa, papillae. Arrow heads indicate ventral papillae. Scale bars: A–B, 2 mm, C–E, 1 mm, F–H, 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552077" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552077/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Body without dorsal tubercles. Ten pairs of elytra on segments 2, 4, 5, 7, and alternating segments up to 19. Elytra transparent, without fringing papillae at outer margins, without microtubercles and macrotubercles. Bilobed prostomium pinkish in live (whitish in ethanol), with distinct anterior lobes; anterior lobes triangular, with conical frontal filaments. Median antenna with short cylindrical ceratophore (
<figureCitation id="13408CDF502AFFD7FC1FF9B1FB963849" box="[1003,1093,1590,1616]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,181,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[164,1423,181,1865]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Branchinotogluma nikkoensis sp. nov., holotype. A, whole specimen, dorsal view; B, whole specimen, ventral view; C, dorsal view of anterior; D, ventral view of posterior; E, elytrum; F, pharynx, frontal view; G, pharynx, lateral view; H, papillae of pharynx. Abbreviation: ma, median antenna; p. palps; tc, tentacular cirri; pa, papillae. Arrow heads indicate ventral papillae. Scale bars: A–B, 2 mm, C–E, 1 mm, F–H, 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552077" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552077/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">Figs 1C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13408CDF502AFFD7FBA6F9B1FBA53849" box="[1106,1142,1590,1616]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1912,1936]" captionTargetBox="[236,1351,194,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[223,1363,181,1889]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Branchinotogluma nikkoensis sp. nov., holotype. A, dorsal view of anterior; B, ventral view of segments 11–21; C, parapodium, right side, chaetiger 10; D, notochaeta, chaetiger 10; E, neurochaeta, chaetiger 10. Scale bars: A–B, 1 mm; C–E, 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552083" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552083/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">3A</figureCitation>
), inserted at anterior notch of prostomium; style 
<quantity id="4C833DBF502AFFD7FE72F9DDFE0D386C" box="[390,478,1626,1653]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="19" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
, not papillate, thin and tapered. Lateral antennae absent. Eyes absent. Palps as long as ventral tentacular cirri (
<figureCitation id="13408CDF502AFFD7FE6DF9F9FE213881" box="[409,498,1662,1688]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,181,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[164,1423,181,1865]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Branchinotogluma nikkoensis sp. nov., holotype. A, whole specimen, dorsal view; B, whole specimen, ventral view; C, dorsal view of anterior; D, ventral view of posterior; E, elytrum; F, pharynx, frontal view; G, pharynx, lateral view; H, papillae of pharynx. Abbreviation: ma, median antenna; p. palps; tc, tentacular cirri; pa, papillae. Arrow heads indicate ventral papillae. Scale bars: A–B, 2 mm, C–E, 1 mm, F–H, 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552077" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552077/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">Figs 1C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13408CDF502AFFD7FE0AF9F9FDF13881" box="[510,546,1662,1688]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1912,1936]" captionTargetBox="[236,1351,194,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[223,1363,181,1889]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Branchinotogluma nikkoensis sp. nov., holotype. A, dorsal view of anterior; B, ventral view of segments 11–21; C, parapodium, right side, chaetiger 10; D, notochaeta, chaetiger 10; E, neurochaeta, chaetiger 10. Scale bars: A–B, 1 mm; C–E, 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552083" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552083/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">3A</figureCitation>
), whitish, smooth. Dorsal and ventral tentacular cirri with tentaculophores lateral to prostomium. Dorsal tentacular cirri longer than ventral tentacular cirri. Dorsal and ventral tentacular cirri whitish, not papillated. One pair of long, thick ventral papillae present on segment 12. Ventral segmental lamellae near ventral bases of neuropodia present on segments 13–17. Pygidium with a pair of pygidial cirri (
<figureCitation id="13408CDF502AFFD7FBA2F96DFB7F391D" box="[1110,1196,1770,1796]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1912,1936]" captionTargetBox="[236,1351,194,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[223,1363,181,1889]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Branchinotogluma nikkoensis sp. nov., holotype. A, dorsal view of anterior; B, ventral view of segments 11–21; C, parapodium, right side, chaetiger 10; D, notochaeta, chaetiger 10; E, neurochaeta, chaetiger 10. Scale bars: A–B, 1 mm; C–E, 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552083" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552083/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC4905A502AFFD1FF33F889FA9E3EE0" blockId="2.[151,1437,1302,2012]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1437,151,789]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="21" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">
Parapodia biramous (
<figureCitation id="13408CDF502AFFD7FE43F889FDC63931" box="[439,533,1806,1832]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1798,1822]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,813,1775]" captionTargetId="figure-297@4.[151,1436,813,1775]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Branchinotogluma nikkoensis sp. nov., holotype. A, parapodium, right side, chaetiger 10; B, dorsal branchiae, chaetiger 10; C, notochaetae, chaetiger 10; D, neurochaetae, chaetiger 10. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552081" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552081/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">Figs 2A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13408CDF502AFFD7FDD6F889FD953931" box="[546,582,1806,1832]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1912,1936]" captionTargetBox="[236,1351,194,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[223,1363,181,1889]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Branchinotogluma nikkoensis sp. nov., holotype. A, dorsal view of anterior; B, ventral view of segments 11–21; C, parapodium, right side, chaetiger 10; D, notochaeta, chaetiger 10; E, neurochaeta, chaetiger 10. Scale bars: A–B, 1 mm; C–E, 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552083" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552083/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">3C</figureCitation>
). Notopodia shorter than neuropodia. Notopodia with short conical acicular lobes, on elytrigerous segments, with prominent bracts enclosing notochaetae dorsally and posteriorly (
<figureCitation id="13408CDF502AFFD7FAF3F8B5FAB23955" box="[1287,1377,1842,1868]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1798,1822]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,813,1775]" captionTargetId="figure-297@4.[151,1436,813,1775]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Branchinotogluma nikkoensis sp. nov., holotype. A, parapodium, right side, chaetiger 10; B, dorsal branchiae, chaetiger 10; C, notochaetae, chaetiger 10; D, neurochaetae, chaetiger 10. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552081" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552081/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">Figs 2B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13408CDF502AFFD7FA9FF8B5FA5C3955" box="[1387,1423,1842,1868]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1912,1936]" captionTargetBox="[236,1351,194,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[223,1363,181,1889]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Branchinotogluma nikkoensis sp. nov., holotype. A, dorsal view of anterior; B, ventral view of segments 11–21; C, parapodium, right side, chaetiger 10; D, notochaeta, chaetiger 10; E, neurochaeta, chaetiger 10. Scale bars: A–B, 1 mm; C–E, 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552083" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552083/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">3C</figureCitation>
). About 50 notochaetae in each notopodium. Notochaetae short to long, with distinct rows of spines along one side, tapering to blunt tips, unidentate, stouter than neurochaetae (
<figureCitation id="13408CDF502AFFD7FCB6F8FDFC4D398D" box="[834,926,1914,1940]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1798,1822]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,813,1775]" captionTargetId="figure-297@4.[151,1436,813,1775]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Branchinotogluma nikkoensis sp. nov., holotype. A, parapodium, right side, chaetiger 10; B, dorsal branchiae, chaetiger 10; C, notochaetae, chaetiger 10; D, neurochaetae, chaetiger 10. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552081" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552081/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">Figs 2C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13408CDF502AFFD7FC5FF8FDFC03398D" box="[939,976,1914,1940]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1912,1936]" captionTargetBox="[236,1351,194,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[223,1363,181,1889]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Branchinotogluma nikkoensis sp. nov., holotype. A, dorsal view of anterior; B, ventral view of segments 11–21; C, parapodium, right side, chaetiger 10; D, notochaeta, chaetiger 10; E, neurochaeta, chaetiger 10. Scale bars: A–B, 1 mm; C–E, 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552083" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552083/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">3D</figureCitation>
). Neuropodia with subconical prechaetal lobes tapering to sharp tips; post chaetal lobes shorter, rounded. Neurochaetae of 
<specimenCount id="9D7D5BD3502AFFD7FBD4F818FB5139A0" box="[1056,1154,1951,1977]" pageId="2" pageNumber="19" type="generic" typeStatus="type">one type</specimenCount>
, numerous, short to long, with borders finely spinous, tips slightly hooked and finely spinous, spines long and widely spaced in sub-distal region, without semi-lunar pockets (
<figureCitation id="13408CDF502CFFD1FDD8FF10FD5A3EA8" box="[556,649,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1798,1822]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,813,1775]" captionTargetId="figure-297@4.[151,1436,813,1775]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Branchinotogluma nikkoensis sp. nov., holotype. A, parapodium, right side, chaetiger 10; B, dorsal branchiae, chaetiger 10; C, notochaetae, chaetiger 10; D, neurochaetae, chaetiger 10. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552081" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552081/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">Figs 2D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13408CDF502CFFD1FD61FF10FD643EA8" box="[661,695,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1912,1936]" captionTargetBox="[236,1351,194,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[223,1363,181,1889]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Branchinotogluma nikkoensis sp. nov., holotype. A, dorsal view of anterior; B, ventral view of segments 11–21; C, parapodium, right side, chaetiger 10; D, notochaeta, chaetiger 10; E, neurochaeta, chaetiger 10. Scale bars: A–B, 1 mm; C–E, 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552083" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552083/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">3E</figureCitation>
). Robust acicula in each rami. Ventral cirri tapered, not papillated, attached on middle part of parapodia. On segment 2, ventral cirri elongated and projecting from half of neuropodia. Branchiae present from chaetigers 3 to 16, short, digitate, with 2–3 filaments, two pouches per parapodium.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF04C0D2502BFFD6FF63F8E6FD2939FC" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552077" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6552077" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552077/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="20" startId="3.[151,250,1889,1913]" targetBox="[164,1423,181,1865]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="8BC4905A502BFFD6FF63F8E6FD2939FC" blockId="3.[151,1436,1889,2022]" pageId="3" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis id="B90F4C48502BFFD6FF63F8E6FEC53960" bold="true" box="[151,278,1889,1913]" pageId="3" pageNumber="20">FIGURE 1.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C7BEBD9502BFFD6FEEAF8E6FD9C3960" authority="Jimi &amp; Chen &amp; Fujiwara, 2022" authorityName="Jimi &amp; Chen &amp; Fujiwara" authorityYear="2022" box="[286,591,1889,1913]" class="Polychaeta" family="Polynoidae" genus="Branchinotogluma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="3" pageNumber="20" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="nikkoensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90F4C48502BFFD6FEEAF8E6FD9C3960" box="[286,591,1889,1913]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="20">Branchinotogluma nikkoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B90F4C48502BFFD6FDACF8E6FD783960" bold="true" box="[600,683,1889,1913]" pageId="3" pageNumber="20">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23CF133502BFFD6FDACF8E6FD783960" box="[600,683,1889,1913]" pageId="3" pageNumber="20" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, holotype. A, whole specimen, dorsal view; B, whole specimen, ventral view; C, dorsal view of anterior; D, ventral view of posterior; E, elytrum; F, pharynx, frontal view; G, pharynx, lateral view; H, papillae of pharynx. Abbreviation: ma, median antenna; p. palps; tc, tentacular cirri; pa, papillae. Arrow heads indicate ventral papillae. Scale bars: A–B, 2 mm, C–E, 1 mm, F–H, 0.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BC4905A502CFFD1FF33FE84FF093F58" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">Pharynx with six pairs of papillae terminally and two pairs of jaws. Jaws growing inwardly, with minute denticles.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC4905A502CFFD1FF33FECDFF093F90" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis id="B90F4C48502CFFD1FF33FECDFEEB3F7D" bold="true" box="[199,312,330,356]" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">Variation</emphasis>
: 
<typeStatus id="54C02EF8502CFFD1FEBEFECCFE643F7C" box="[330,439,331,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">Paratypes</typeStatus>
<quantity id="4C833DBF502CFFD1FE35FECCFDE33F7C" box="[449,560,331,357]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" unit="mm" value="8.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="7.0">7–10 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="4C833DBF502CFFD1FD89FECCFD113F7C" box="[637,706,331,357]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
wide without chaetae. Ventral papillae absent in female specimens.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C361C3D1502CFFD1FF33FE14FB2D3FB4" box="[199,1278,403,429]" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BC4905A502CFFD1FF33FE14FB2D3FB4" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,789]" box="[199,1278,403,429]" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis id="B90F4C48502CFFD1FF33FE14FE9B3FB4" bold="true" box="[199,328,403,429]" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">Etymology</emphasis>
: Named after the 
<typeStatus id="54C02EF8502CFFD1FDE6FE14FD913FB4" box="[530,578,403,429]" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">type</typeStatus>
locality (Nikko Seamount). The specific name is an adjective.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C361C3D1502CFFD1FF33FE31FB0A3FC8" box="[199,1241,438,465]" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BC4905A502CFFD1FF33FE31FB0A3FC8" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,789]" box="[199,1241,438,465]" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis id="B90F4C48502CFFD1FF33FE31FEB03FC9" bold="true" box="[199,355,438,464]" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">Distribution:</emphasis>
Hydrothermal vent, 
<quantity id="4C833DBF502CFFD1FDB8FE31FD463FC8" box="[588,661,438,465]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.58" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" unit="m" value="458.0">458 m</quantity>
, Nikko Seamount, 
<collectingCountry id="F36CD0CA502CFFD1FC98FE30FC7C3FC8" box="[876,943,439,465]" name="Japan" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">Japan</collectingCountry>
, Northwest Pacific Ocean.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C361C3D1502CFFD1FF33FE5CFA933D0C" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC4905A502CFFD1FF33FE5CFA933D0C" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis id="B90F4C48502CFFD1FF33FE5CFEE73FEC" bold="true" box="[199,308,475,501]" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">Remarks</emphasis>
: This new species resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C7BEBD9502CFFD1FD7CFE5CFBA73FEC" authority="Pettibone, 1985" authorityName="Pettibone" authorityYear="1985" box="[648,1140,474,501]" class="Polychaeta" family="Polynoidae" genus="Branchinotogluma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="hessleri">
<emphasis id="B90F4C48502CFFD1FD7CFE5CFC693FEC" box="[648,954,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">Branchinotogluma hessleri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFEAEDAB502CFFD1FC36FE5CFBA73FEC" author="Pettibone, M. H." box="[962,1140,474,501]" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" pagination="447 - 469" refId="ref6414" refString="Pettibone, M. H. (1985) Additional branchiate scale-worms (Polychaeta: Polynoidae) from Galapagos hydrothermal vent and rift-area off western Mexico at 21 ° N. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 98, 447 - 469." type="journal article" year="1985">
Pettibone, 
<quantity id="4C833DBF502CFFD1FBC8FE5DFBA73FEC" box="[1084,1140,474,501]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0419" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" unit="in" value="1985.0">1985</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in having a body with 21 segments, long and thick ventral papillae, bilobed prostomium, dentated jaws. The new species can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C7BEBD9502CFFD1FF20FDA4FE9A3C24" authorityName="Pettibone" authorityYear="1985" box="[212,329,547,573]" class="Polychaeta" family="Polynoidae" genus="Branchinotogluma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="hessleri">
<emphasis id="B90F4C48502CFFD1FF20FDA4FE9A3C24" box="[212,329,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">B. hessleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the following features: 
<emphasis id="B90F4C48502CFFD1FD87FDA4FDA83C25" box="[627,635,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">i</emphasis>
) ventral segmental lamellae near ventral bases of neuropodia present on segments 13–17; 
<emphasis id="B90F4C48502CFFD1FEA8FDC0FEBF3C79" box="[348,364,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">ii</emphasis>
) dorsal tentacular cirri longer than ventral tentacular cirri; 
<emphasis id="B90F4C48502CFFD1FBF7FDC0FBC93C79" box="[1027,1050,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">iii</emphasis>
) dorsal tubercles absent. 
<taxonomicName id="4C7BEBD9502CFFD1FACDFDC0FD153C9C" authority="(Miura &amp; Hashimoto, 1991)" baseAuthorityName="Miura &amp; Hashimoto" baseAuthorityYear="1991" class="Polychaeta" family="Polynoidae" genus="Branchinotogluma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis id="B90F4C48502CFFD1FACDFDC0FE503C9D" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">Branchinotogluma japonicus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFEAEDAB502CFFD1FE66FDECFD6D3C9C" author="Miura, T. &amp; Hashimoto, J." box="[402,702,619,645]" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" pagination="166 - 174" refId="ref6283" refString="Miura, T. &amp; Hashimoto, J. (1991) Two new branchiate scaleworms (Polynoidae: Polychaeta) from the hydrothermal vent of the Okinawa Trough and the volcanic seamount off Chichijima Island. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 104, 166 - 174." type="journal article" year="1991">Miura &amp; Hashimoto, 1991</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
is known from the Kaikata Seamount on the Izu-Ogasawara Arc and vents in the 
<collectingRegion id="49BF5EB8502CFFD1FEA1FD08FE693CB0" box="[341,442,655,681]" country="Japan" name="Okinawa" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">Okinawa</collectingRegion>
Trough (Zhang 
<emphasis id="B90F4C48502CFFD1FD82FD08FD7A3CB0" box="[630,681,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">et al</emphasis>
. 2018) but has not been found in Nikko Seamount which is much further south to the Kaikata Seamount. 
<taxonomicName id="4C7BEBD9502CFFD1FDB8FD34FB263CD4" authority="Zhang, Chen &amp; Qiu, 2018" authorityName="Zhang, Chen &amp; Qiu" authorityYear="2018" box="[588,1269,691,717]" class="Polychaeta" family="Polynoidae" genus="Branchinotogluma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="elytropapillata">
<emphasis id="B90F4C48502CFFD1FDB8FD34FC1A3CD4" box="[588,969,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">Branchinotogluma elytropapillata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFEAEDAB502CFFD1FC24FD34FB263CD4" author="Zhang, Y. &amp; Chen, C. &amp; Qiu, J. - W." box="[976,1269,691,717]" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" pagination="112" refId="ref7045" refString="Zhang, Y., Chen, C. &amp; Qiu, J. - W. (2018) Sexually dimorphic scale worms (Annelida: Polynoidae) from hydrothermal vents in the Okinawa Trough: two new species and two new sex morphs. Frontiers in Marine Science, 5, 112. https: // doi. org / 10.3389 / fmars. 2018.00112" type="journal article" year="2018">Zhang, Chen &amp; Qiu, 2018</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, was described from the 
<collectingRegion id="49BF5EB8502CFFD1FEF4FD50FEB63CE8" box="[256,357,727,753]" country="Japan" name="Okinawa" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">Okinawa</collectingRegion>
Trough and also has not been found at Nikko Seamount. The new species can be differentiated from these two other known Japanese species by having elytra with smooth edges and jaws with denticles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
